chart_description: This chart monitors the system's memory usage level when the system is experiencing some pressure. Some pressure is measured by the operating system's algorithms when the memory pressure is not significant but still above the ideal level.

dimension_descriptions.some 10: The percentage of pressure on the memory when some applications or system processes are requesting memory.
dimension_descriptions.some 300: The pressure percentage of the memory when more applications or system processes are requesting memory.
dimension_descriptions.some 60: The percentage of memory pressure when the system memory becomes critical, and many applications or system processes are requesting memory.
